Layouts

Layouts define the CSS grid structure for the app. Each layout is a tiddler tagged `$:/tags/rimir/appify/layout`.

Available layouts:

<$list filter="[all[shadows+tiddlers]tag[$:/tags/rimir/appify/layout]]">
- <$view field="caption"/> — slots: <$view field="appify-slots"/>
</$list>

Switching layouts:

Change the `appify-layout` field on the app tiddler:
```
set_field(title="<appTitle>", field="appify-layout", value="sidebar-main")
```

After switching, update `appify-view-<slot>` fields for the new layout's slots. Old slot bindings from the previous layout are preserved (in case the user switches back).

Layout tiddler fields:

- `appify-slots`: space-separated slot names
- `appify-grid-areas`: CSS grid-template-areas value
- `appify-grid-columns`: CSS grid-template-columns value
- `appify-grid-rows`: CSS grid-template-rows value
- `caption`: display name

See also: llm_help("appify/proportions") — customizing column/row sizes, llm_help("appify/splits") — subdividing slots into panes
